\zeta^{(j=0)}_2=0.68\n\\pm 0.01$, $\\zeta^{(j=1)}_2=1.0\\pm 0.15$ and $\\zeta^{(j=2)}_2=1.38 \\pm 0.10$.\nWe present theoretical arguments for the values of these exponents usingthe\nClebsch representation of the Euler equations; neglecting anomalous\ncorrections, the values obtained are 2/3, 1 and 4/3 respectively.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 24 Jun 1999 05:38:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-10-31"}
